# IWP Implementation

When an IWP file is the task:

1. Treat the IWP as the complete implementation prompt.
2. Read governing ARP/AEP documents from `86-vibe-platform/architecture/`.
3. Inspect the existing baseline in `86-vibe-cli` before adding or changing files.
4. Implement all code and tests in **86-vibe-cli** — never in `86-vibe-platform`.
5. Do not implement unrelated platform services named outside the IWP scope.
6. Follow ARP-001-05 engineering coding standards.
7. Verify with `pytest` from the `86-vibe-cli` root.

## Do not implement in 86-vibe-example

IWP packages target the CLI implementation repository unless the IWP explicitly names `86-vibe-example` as the implementation target.

## Prompt pattern

> Implement IWP-00X-YY from this document. Put all code changes in `86-vibe-cli`. Run `pytest` when done.
